Examples

// Create a start state circle
var startState = new EllipseElement("start")
{
    Position = new Point(50, 100),
    Width = 30,
    Height = 30,
    Fill = "#2ecc71",
    Stroke = "#27ae60",
    StrokeWidth = 2
};

// Create an oval annotation
var oval = new EllipseElement("highlight")
{
    Position = new Point(100, 200),
    Width = 150,
    Height = 80,
    Fill = null,  // No fill
    Stroke = "#e74c3c",
    StrokeWidth = 3
};

Remarks

Ellipses are useful for: - State diagram start/end states - Circular annotations - Icon backgrounds - Decision points

The ellipse is defined by its bounding box (Position, Width, Height). For a perfect circle, set Width == Height.

Remarks

Used by renderer registries to select the appropriate renderer. For nodes, this typically comes from the node definition's Type property. For shapes, this identifies the shape type (line, rectangle, text, etc.).
